<subSubSection id="40A284DDFFB9FFBFFF5AFB15FC2B374E" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="427" pageId="13" pageNumber="426" type="key">
<keyStep id="B34CCFF3FFB9FFBCFF5AFB15FC163391" pageId="13" pageNumber="426">
<paragraph id="0807D756FFB9FFBCFF5AFB15FC17333F" blockId="13.[148,977,1231,1570]" pageId="13" pageNumber="426">
<keyLead id="B3497463FFB9FFBCFF5AFB15FC17333F" pageId="13" pageNumber="426">
1 Antenna with club with apical pilose part about one-third length of basal glabrous part (
<figureCitation id="9083CBD3FFB9FFBCFF29FB33FEF732F2" box="[231,304,1257,1278]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="11.[169,208,648,667]" captionTargetBox="[149,980,195,627]" captionTargetId="figure-434@11.[148,981,194,627]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs. 30–34. Daisya obriani, male. 30) Head, lateral view; 31) antenna, lateral view; 32) scutellum, dorsal view; 33) tarsus, front, dorsal view; 34) femora and tibia, front, anterior view. Scale line ¼ 1.0 mm, except tarsus and scutellum, 0.63 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="426">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
). Male with inner margin of front femur with distinct tooth at apical one-third. (
<figureCitation id="9083CBD3FFB9FFBCFEEEFADEFEAC3315" box="[288,363,1284,1305]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="11.[169,208,648,667]" captionTargetBox="[149,980,195,627]" captionTargetId="figure-434@11.[148,981,194,627]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs. 30–34. Daisya obriani, male. 30) Head, lateral view; 31) antenna, lateral view; 32) scutellum, dorsal view; 33) tarsus, front, dorsal view; 34) femora and tibia, front, anterior view. Scale line ¼ 1.0 mm, except tarsus and scutellum, 0.63 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="426">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
). Elytra black with small, indistinct reddish marking at lateral margin at basal one-third 
<subScript id="943CD513FFB9FFBCFE7AFAFDFD38333C" attach="right" box="[436,767,1319,1328]" fontSize="4" pageId="13" pageNumber="426">- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -</subScript>
<taxonomicName id="CFB8ACD5FFB9FFBCFCC9FAC4FC17333F" authority="Anderson" authorityName="Anderson" authorityYear="2003" box="[775,976,1310,1331]" class="Insecta" family="Dryophthoridae" genus="Daisya" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obriani">
<emphasis id="3ACC0B44FFB9FFBCFCC9FAC4FCAB333F" box="[775,876,1310,1331]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="426">D. obriani</emphasis>
Anderson
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0807D756FFB9FFBCFF5AFAE3FC163391" blockId="13.[148,977,1231,1570]" pageId="13" pageNumber="426">
<keyLead id="B3497463FFB9FFBCFF5AFAE3FC163391" pageId="13" pageNumber="426">
19 Antenna with club with apical pilose part one-quarter to one-fifth length of basal glabrous part (
<figureCitation id="9083CBD3FFB9FFBCFE8DFA89FE523364" box="[323,405,1363,1384]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="12.[197,236,628,647]" captionTargetBox="[176,1007,196,607]" captionTargetId="figure-384@12.[175,1007,194,607]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figs. 35–44. Daisya andersonae. 35) Head, male, lateral view; 36) head, male, dorsal view; 37) Head, female, lateral view; 38) antenna, male, lateral view; 39) tarsus, front, male, dorsal view; 40) pronotum, male, dorsal view; 41) femora and tibia, front, male, anterior view; 42) tergite 8 and sternite 8, male, ventral view; 43) aedeagus, male, dorsal view; 44) aedeagus, male, lateral view. Scale line ¼ 1.0 mm, except tarsus, 0.63 mm, and pronotum, 1.55 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="426">Figs. 38</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="9083CBD3FFB9FFBCFE6CFA89FE7A3364" box="[418,445,1363,1384]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="13.[170,209,888,907]" captionTargetBox="[145,977,196,866]" captionTargetId="figure-433@13.[145,978,194,867]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figs. 45–52. Daisya huetheri. 45) Head, male, lateral view; 46) head, male, dorsal view; 47) head, female, lateral view; 48) head, female, dorsal view; 49) antenna, male, lateral view; 50) tarsus, front, male, dorsal view; 51) pronotum, male, dorsal view; 52) femora and tibia, front, male, anterior view. Scale line ¼ 1.0 mm, except tarsus, 0.63 mm, and pronotum, 1.55 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="426">49</figureCitation>
). Male with inner margin of front femur with angular swelling at apical one-third (
<figureCitation id="9083CBD3FFB9FFBCFE16FAB4FDEA338F" box="[472,557,1390,1411]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="12.[197,236,628,647]" captionTargetBox="[176,1007,196,607]" captionTargetId="figure-384@12.[175,1007,194,607]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figs. 35–44. Daisya andersonae. 35) Head, male, lateral view; 36) head, male, dorsal view; 37) Head, female, lateral view; 38) antenna, male, lateral view; 39) tarsus, front, male, dorsal view; 40) pronotum, male, dorsal view; 41) femora and tibia, front, male, anterior view; 42) tergite 8 and sternite 8, male, ventral view; 43) aedeagus, male, dorsal view; 44) aedeagus, male, lateral view. Scale line ¼ 1.0 mm, except tarsus, 0.63 mm, and pronotum, 1.55 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="426">Figs. 41</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="9083CBD3FFB9FFBCFDF2FAB4FD90338F" box="[572,599,1390,1411]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="13.[170,209,888,907]" captionTargetBox="[145,977,196,866]" captionTargetId="figure-433@13.[145,978,194,867]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figs. 45–52. Daisya huetheri. 45) Head, male, lateral view; 46) head, male, dorsal view; 47) head, female, lateral view; 48) head, female, dorsal view; 49) antenna, male, lateral view; 50) tarsus, front, male, dorsal view; 51) pronotum, male, dorsal view; 52) femora and tibia, front, male, anterior view. Scale line ¼ 1.0 mm, except tarsus, 0.63 mm, and pronotum, 1.55 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="426">52</figureCitation>
). Elytra black with extensive reddish markings 
<subScript id="943CD513FFB9FFBCFEDDFA4BFC7B3396" attach="left" box="[275,956,1425,1434]" fontSize="4" pageId="13" pageNumber="426">- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -</subScript>
2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="B34CCFF3FFB9FFBFFF5AFA79FC2B374E" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="427" pageId="13" pageNumber="426">
<paragraph id="0807D756FFB9FFBCFF5AFA79FC17302E" blockId="13.[148,977,1231,1570]" pageId="13" pageNumber="426">
<keyLead id="B3497463FFB9FFBCFF5AFA79FC17302E" pageId="13" pageNumber="426">
2 Tarsus with article 3 about as long as wide, about one and one-half times width of article 2; sub-cordiform, maximum width near apex, lateral margins distinctly convergent towards base (
<figureCitation id="9083CBD3FFB9FFBCFE72FA02FDCD33E1" box="[444,522,1496,1517]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="12.[197,236,628,647]" captionTargetBox="[176,1007,196,607]" captionTargetId="figure-384@12.[175,1007,194,607]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figs. 35–44. Daisya andersonae. 35) Head, male, lateral view; 36) head, male, dorsal view; 37) Head, female, lateral view; 38) antenna, male, lateral view; 39) tarsus, front, male, dorsal view; 40) pronotum, male, dorsal view; 41) femora and tibia, front, male, anterior view; 42) tergite 8 and sternite 8, male, ventral view; 43) aedeagus, male, dorsal view; 44) aedeagus, male, lateral view. Scale line ¼ 1.0 mm, except tarsus, 0.63 mm, and pronotum, 1.55 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="426">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
). Male rostrum with only moderately coarse punctures (
<figureCitation id="9083CBD3FFB9FFBCFEFDFA29FE793004" box="[307,446,1523,1544]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="12.[197,236,628,647]" captionTargetBox="[176,1007,196,607]" captionTargetId="figure-384@12.[175,1007,194,607]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figs. 35–44. Daisya andersonae. 35) Head, male, lateral view; 36) head, male, dorsal view; 37) Head, female, lateral view; 38) antenna, male, lateral view; 39) tarsus, front, male, dorsal view; 40) pronotum, male, dorsal view; 41) femora and tibia, front, male, anterior view; 42) tergite 8 and sternite 8, male, ventral view; 43) aedeagus, male, dorsal view; 44) aedeagus, male, lateral view. Scale line ¼ 1.0 mm, except tarsus, 0.63 mm, and pronotum, 1.55 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="426">Figs. 35–36</figureCitation>
); female rostrum finely punctate (
<figureCitation id="9083CBD3FFB9FFBCFCA0FA29FC0D3004" box="[878,970,1523,1544]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="12.[197,236,628,647]" captionTargetBox="[176,1007,196,607]" captionTargetId="figure-384@12.[175,1007,194,607]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figs. 35–44. Daisya andersonae. 35) Head, male, lateral view; 36) head, male, dorsal view; 37) Head, female, lateral view; 38) antenna, male, lateral view; 39) tarsus, front, male, dorsal view; 40) pronotum, male, dorsal view; 41) femora and tibia, front, male, anterior view; 42) tergite 8 and sternite 8, male, ventral view; 43) aedeagus, male, dorsal view; 44) aedeagus, male, lateral view. Scale line ¼ 1.0 mm, except tarsus, 0.63 mm, and pronotum, 1.55 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="426">Fig. 37</figureCitation>
) 
<subScript id="943CD513FFB9FFBCFF7FF9CCFD113013" attach="right" box="[177,726,1558,1567]" fontSize="4" pageId="13" pageNumber="426">- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -</subScript>
<taxonomicName id="CFB8ACD5FFB9FFBCFD10F9D7FC17302E" authority="Anderson" authorityName="Anderson" authorityYear="2003" box="[734,976,1549,1570]" class="Insecta" family="Dryophthoridae" genus="Daisya" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andersonae">
<emphasis id="3ACC0B44FFB9FFBCFD10F9D7FCAB302E" box="[734,876,1549,1570]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="426">D. andersonae</emphasis>
Anderson
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0807D756FFBAFFBFFF61FF18FC2B374E" blockId="14.[175,1005,194,322]" pageId="14" pageNumber="427">
<keyLead id="B3497463FFBAFFBFFF61FF18FC2B374E" pageId="14" pageNumber="427">
29 Tarsus with article 3 longer than wide, only slightly wider than width of article 2; sub-oval, maximum width towards midlength, lateral margins arcuate (
<figureCitation id="9083CBD3FFBAFFBFFC58FF07FC2536FE" box="[918,994,221,242]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="13.[170,209,888,907]" captionTargetBox="[145,977,196,866]" captionTargetId="figure-433@13.[145,978,194,867]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figs. 45–52. Daisya huetheri. 45) Head, male, lateral view; 46) head, male, dorsal view; 47) head, female, lateral view; 48) head, female, dorsal view; 49) antenna, male, lateral view; 50) tarsus, front, male, dorsal view; 51) pronotum, male, dorsal view; 52) femora and tibia, front, male, anterior view. Scale line ¼ 1.0 mm, except tarsus, 0.63 mm, and pronotum, 1.55 mm." pageId="14" pageNumber="427">Fig. 50</figureCitation>
). Male and female each with rostrum with distinct dorsal median carina, bordered laterally by row of sunken contiguous punctures throughout length (
<figureCitation id="9083CBD3FFBAFFBFFCBEFEC8FC21372B" box="[880,998,274,295]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="13.[170,209,888,907]" captionTargetBox="[145,977,196,866]" captionTargetId="figure-433@13.[145,978,194,867]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figs. 45–52. Daisya huetheri. 45) Head, male, lateral view; 46) head, male, dorsal view; 47) head, female, lateral view; 48) head, female, dorsal view; 49) antenna, male, lateral view; 50) tarsus, front, male, dorsal view; 51) pronotum, male, dorsal view; 52) femora and tibia, front, male, anterior view. Scale line ¼ 1.0 mm, except tarsus, 0.63 mm, and pronotum, 1.55 mm." pageId="14" pageNumber="427">Figs. 45–48</figureCitation>
) 
<subScript id="943CD513FFBAFFBFFF1AFEEFFCCA3732" attach="right" box="[212,781,309,318]" fontSize="4" pageId="14" pageNumber="427">- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -</subScript>
